<P><H1 align=center>EMPLOYMENT SUMMARY – DC160</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>              
          </P>
<P>This screen shows a summary of the applicant’s employment details and 
salary.</P>
<P><H3>Add: </H3>click on the Add button to enter the 
employment details on screen <A HREF="HELP_DC170.asp">Add / Edit Employment Details (DC170)</A>.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Edit: </H3>to amend existing employment details, 
highlight the entry in the history box and click the Edit button. This will take 
you to screen <A HREF="HELP_DC170.asp">DC170</A> where you can change details as required.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Delete: </H3>to delete a record, highlight it and click 
the Delete button.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Current Highest Tax Rate: </H3>Select the tax rate 
currently applicable to the applicant from the drop down list. This information 
will be provided by the applicant.
<P></P>
<P><H3>UK tax payer: </H3>Is the applicant currently paying UK 
tax. Total Gross and Net Monthly income will be pre-populated from a previous 
screen. Click the Tax Details arrow, which will take you to a screen to record 
details of the applicants tax office, reference number and National Insurance 
number and residency status for tax purposes (I.e. whether the applicant pays 
tax outside the UK). 
<P></P>
